                <h1>Fascinating Facts About Andrew Jackson</h1>
                <p>Andrew Jackson, the 7th U.S. President, served from 1829 to 1837 and was a key figure in American politics. Known for founding the Democratic Party, he was a war hero from the Battle of New Orleans. His policies, however, are controversial, notably the Indian Removal Act, which led to the Trail of Tears. Jackson's strong personality and populism reshaped the presidency.</p>
